				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">But if thats a bug, then why do they let you use bows with that kind of range.?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Believe me, when they were making the bows you speak of, it was never intended that someone of your level would have one. If you're hunting in FoB then by natural progression in the game you should probably be using a store bought bow with no stats and a range of about 75. 
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I've found that sometimes you'll fire arrows and they can get stuck on walls when you're cornering while pulling. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
That's just a display bug. It doesn't actually effect your dps. Once they stick, they stick for good and they don't find their targets later.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=587400" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://mywebspace.sac.winfirst.com/jgrant/public_html/kinv_sig.JPG"></a>
